It's not very efficient, but I'm wondering about the reason. I've stayed tuned to the documentation about CRC32 here:

http://php.net/manual/function.crc32.php

They don't already warn about this action, but on the documentation about the php-module libstdc++ they warn about this:

“As stated underneath 64-bit compilations, the only guarantee libstdc++48 makes for types larger than int is that types larger than int will be larger than int. If in doubt, rebuild your PHP binary against your desired C++ runtime”

I honestly do not know if this is different from 32 bit to 64 bit or is a little change in RFC for CRC32 algorithm or if it is a bugs about the statement, but I don’t think it will be an RFC change”
